tests.name: testConcurrency
tests.stdout:
10:00:45.679 [main] WARN  org.asteriskjava.lock.Locker - Already enabled
917196 Locker  per second with 2 threads and diags
10:00:48.680 [main] WARN  org.asteriskjava.lock.Locker - Will dump Lock stats each minute when there is contention...
10:00:48.681 [main] WARN  org.asteriskjava.lock.Locker - Lock checking disabled
1483296 Locker  per second with 2 threads
11472002 synchronized  per second with 2 threads

It seems wrong that 2 threads with diags is faster,
but the reality is that with the added overhead of diags there is less lock contention so it runs faster.
If more threads are added the two tests produce near identicaly through put as contention is high for both cases then.
